cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY 

Reasoning: 
1) cs.RO (Robotics): The paper focuses on developing a perception and control framework for robots to manipulate flexible cables. 
2) cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper uses a vision-based tactile sensor, GelSight, to estimate the pose of the cable in the grip. 
3) cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper uses a learned linear model of the cable sliding dynamics for the cable pose controller. 
4) cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes a framework for robots to accomplish the task of following a cable using tactile feedback. 
5) cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper develops two tactile-based controllers for cable grip and cable pose, which involve control theory and system dynamics.
